1. The identity (no change), which fixes all \(6^4 = 1296\) colorings.
2. 120° and 240° rotations, which each fix \(6^2 = 36\) colorings (since each rotation cycle involves 3 triangles, which must be the same color, and the fourth triangle can be any of 6 colors).
3. 3 reflections, which each fix \(6^3 = 216\) colorings (since each reflection cycle involves 2 matching triangles, and the other two can be any of 6 colors).

